The high court in Nakuru will on Friday give direction on whether a case challenging a directive by the head of public service Joseph Kinyua asking all civil servants to be vaccinated against covid 19 by the 23rd of august will be heard in Nakuru or Nairobi. Justice prof Joel Ngugi, will also give away forward on whether the case will be consolidated with others. The attorney general is arguing that the case is a matter to be heard by the employment and labour relations court. The case challenging Kinyua's directive, has been filed by clement Koigi through his lawyer Kipkoech Ngetich.